Use the standard library
This is how to largest_smallest_integers of lst:
   Remember that largest is []
   Remember that smallest is []
   Remember that n is lst's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that x is item i in lst
      When x is less than 0, then:
         When smallest is [], then:
            Remember that smallest is x
         But, if not:
            When x is more than smallest, then:
               Remember that smallest is x
            End when
         End when
      End when
      When x is more than 0, then:
         When smallest is [], then:
            Remember that largest is x
         But, if not:
            When largest is [], then:
               Remember that largest is x
            But, if not:
               When x is less than largest, then:
                  Remember that largest is x
               End when
            End when
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is [largest, smallest]
Now you know
>>> largest_smallest_integers of [2, 4, 1, 3, 5, 7] 
[[], 1]
>>> largest_smallest_integers of [] 
[[], []]
>>> largest_smallest_integers of [0] 
[[], []]